Look at her face.
As soon as I said eight months...

247
00:09:09,282 --> 00:09:11,785
Look at her face.
As soon as I said eight months...

248
00:09:11,851 --> 00:09:13,186
Let's use that as an insert.

249
00:09:13,253 --> 00:09:14,487
I don't blame her, though.

250
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:16,890
- There's a lot of waiting time,
- It can't be helped.

251
00:09:16,956 --> 00:09:18,458
and other inconveniences too.

252
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,693
Is it easier to film in summer or winter?

253
00:09:21,294 --> 00:09:22,362
They're both hard.

254
00:09:22,962 --> 00:09:25,165
Wait, I really need to hear
from Soo-jung first.

255
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,299
Come on, spill the tea.

256
00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:27,567
Do you want a beer?

257
00:09:27,634 --> 00:09:28,701
- Just be honest.
- Tell us.

258
00:09:28,768 --> 00:09:29,769
- You need a beer?
- Maybe I should have a drink.

259
00:09:29,836 --> 00:09:31,204
- Yeah?
- You need a drink?

260
00:09:31,271 --> 00:09:32,338
- Let's have a glass each, then.
- Let's get you one.

261
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:33,873
- Do you want a glass?
- It's a genuine question.

262
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:36,076
- Do you want one?
- No, I can't drink beer.

263
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:38,144
Okay. Then let's get our respective drinks

264
00:09:38,211 --> 00:09:39,679
- and make a toast.
- Okay.

265
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:41,347
- Goodness.
- Let's make a toast.

266
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:43,249
- You can have this.
- It's okay. They'll give me one.

267
00:09:43,316 --> 00:09:44,818
- I see.
- After we make the toast,

268
00:09:44,884 --> 00:09:47,454
- ask me to do a love shot with Jun-han.
- There are seven sisters.

269
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:51,057
- Just start chanting it.
- Su-ji and Yi-rang are the older sisters.

270
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:52,625
I'll make some token protests
and then do it.

271
00:09:52,692 --> 00:09:53,526
- Is that right?
- Hey.

272
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:56,262
- Why don't we do our club's usual chant?
- Okay.

273
00:09:56,329 --> 00:09:57,764
- Okay, let's do it.
- We all know it, right?

274
00:09:57,897 --> 00:09:59,499
Legwork today,

275
00:09:59,566 --> 00:10:01,568
- building owner tomorrow!
- Building owner tomorrow!

276
00:10:01,634 --> 00:10:02,569
- Cheers!
- Drink up.

277
00:10:02,635 --> 00:10:04,671
- You guys should do a love shot.
- Oh, stop it.

278
00:10:04,737 --> 00:10:07,707
- Love shot!
- Come on, don't make me do this!

279
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,209
- Love shot!
- Love shot!

280
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:10,777
Love shot...

281
00:10:12,479 --> 00:10:13,546
Are you okay?

282
00:10:14,781 --> 00:10:15,815
Is this real?

283
00:10:15,882 --> 00:10:17,150
Thank you, Soo-jung.

284
00:10:17,217 --> 00:10:19,452
- Thanks a lot.
- Let us do one too.

285
00:10:23,089 --> 00:10:24,924
- Anyway--
- Wait a minute.

286
00:10:24,991 --> 00:10:26,559
- Look at Eun-kyung.
- What?

287
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,095
- No, I--
- She looks like a deer in the headlights.

288
00:10:29,162 --> 00:10:30,964
- Goodness.
- Can I just take a moment?

289
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:32,465
I need to take a moment.

290
00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:33,666
Take a moment where?

291
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:34,834
- Excuse me for a minute.
- It's...

292
00:10:34,901 --> 00:10:37,237
<i>- </i>It's because we haven't met in a while.
- What is she doing?

293
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:38,438
It's understandable.

294
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:40,006
We're all lively
since we haven't met in a while.

295
00:10:40,073 --> 00:10:41,875
Usually, the four would meet...

296
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:43,176
Is this how it always is?

297
00:10:43,243 --> 00:10:44,944
Come to think of it...

298
00:10:45,011 --> 00:10:46,246
It's exhausting for me too.

299
00:10:46,946 --> 00:10:48,181
It's really exhausting.

300
00:10:48,381 --> 00:10:49,482
- Really?
- Yes.

301
00:10:49,549 --> 00:10:50,416
I see.

302
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:51,885
You didn't come here because you heard
we had Dubai chewy cookies, did you?

303
00:10:51,951 --> 00:10:52,785
Did you?

304
00:10:52,852 --> 00:10:54,320
- Let's do our best!
- Yes.

305
00:10:54,854 --> 00:10:56,756
The official meeting
is the day after tomorrow, right?

306
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:57,657
- Right.
- Right.

307
00:10:57,724 --> 00:10:59,325
- So why did we meet up early?
- Yes. Why?

308
00:10:59,526 --> 00:11:02,128
- Well, the thing is...
- Yes?

309
00:11:02,462 --> 00:11:03,496
We've been

310
00:11:04,264 --> 00:11:06,166
- talking about some things
- Yes?

311
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:11,171
that happened
while we were doing club activities,

312
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,406
and well...

313
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:14,874
Did you have a fight?

314
00:11:15,742 --> 00:11:17,911
- Well, no but...
- Did you get into a fistfight?

315
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:19,379
No, we didn't fight.

316
00:11:19,779 --> 00:11:21,114
But Jung-woo has something to say.

317
00:11:21,481 --> 00:11:22,515
I do?

318
00:11:23,283 --> 00:11:25,084
- What is this about?
- He looks like

319
00:11:25,151 --> 00:11:26,419
he has no idea what you're talking about.

320
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:27,587
You have something to say to us?

321
00:11:27,654 --> 00:11:29,923
Let's hear it, then. Don't hold back.

322
00:11:30,890 --> 00:11:32,292
This conversation is all over the place.

323
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:33,560
- It isn't.
- That's not true.

324
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:36,196
It's your turn to talk,
but you forgot your lines!

325
00:11:36,796 --> 00:11:38,531
- We're all waiting for you!
- It was your turn.

326
00:11:38,965 --> 00:11:39,966
Didn't I say my lines already?

327
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:40,934
You did, but--

328
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,735
Is this an editing problem?

329
00:11:46,472 --> 00:11:48,274
- We were waiting.
- It doesn't matter. I can say it again.

330
00:11:48,341 --> 00:11:49,776
- Yes, do that.
- Well,

331
00:11:49,842 --> 00:11:52,579
I want us to stop pretending to be
newlyweds when we do legwork.

332
00:11:52,645 --> 00:11:55,215
I'd rather we didn't do that anymore.
What do you think?

333
00:11:55,748 --> 00:11:59,285
<i>They pretended to be a married couple</i>
<i>whenever they did fieldwork.</i>

334
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:02,422
To be honest, I really liked doing it.

335
00:12:02,622 --> 00:12:04,357
But I guess it weighed on my mind

336
00:12:04,424 --> 00:12:08,161
that we were basically lying our way
onto those properties.

337
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:10,263
So many people are doing that these days.

338
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:12,065
Exactly. Everyone does it.

339
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:13,433
You pretend you're newlyweds

340
00:12:13,499 --> 00:12:16,135
or a mother and daughter
looking for a studio apartment.

341
00:12:16,202 --> 00:12:18,504
I mean, we could be newlyweds, can't we?

342
00:12:20,273 --> 00:12:21,241
I'm not sure.

343
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:23,776
- Come here, you.
- You look good together.

344
00:12:24,644 --> 00:12:26,446
- You two being a married couple?
- We'll look good together.

345
00:12:26,512 --> 00:12:27,914
- What are you talking about?
- We'll look good together.

346
00:12:27,981 --> 00:12:29,415
- We could be newlyweds during legwork.
- Right.

347
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:31,217
Do you like the bedroom, honey?

348
00:12:31,284 --> 00:12:33,786
Her voice completely changed.

349
00:12:34,721 --> 00:12:36,889
I want the window to face south, though.

350
00:12:36,956 --> 00:12:38,124
- Do you?
- Yes.

351
00:12:39,225 --> 00:12:41,561
The window in the bedroom?

352
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:42,462
Yes.

353
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:45,331
He looks so pale and frightened
because of you, Sun-ja.

354
00:12:46,165 --> 00:12:48,534
I told you this won't fool them at all!

355
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:50,937
- You have to play your role!
- The thing is...

356
00:12:51,004 --> 00:12:53,706
That's how we get all the good information
about these properties.

357
00:12:56,576 --> 00:12:59,479
If you don't want her to play your wife,
I could do it instead.

358
00:12:59,679 --> 00:13:00,647
Sure.

359
00:13:00,713 --> 00:13:02,915
Okay. Really?

360
00:13:02,982 --> 00:13:04,050
You're okay with me?

361
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:05,818
- Really?
- What does she have that I don't?

362
00:13:05,885 --> 00:13:07,587
Do you prefer people
who are more voluptuous?

363
00:13:07,654 --> 00:13:10,757
It's just a refreshing change of pace.

364
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:12,492
We've been partners for so long, Yi-rang--

365
00:13:12,558 --> 00:13:14,294
I mean, Sun-ja--

366
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,695
- I'm Sun-ja!
- I'm Sun-i!

367
00:13:15,762 --> 00:13:17,096
- I'm Sun-ja!
- I'm Sun-i!

368
00:13:17,163 --> 00:13:18,464
- Since when?
- It's confusing, right?

369
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:19,899
I'm Sun-i, and she's Sun-ja.

370
00:13:19,966 --> 00:13:21,567
Since when, though?

371
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:24,037
This is the problem with elderly guests.

372
00:13:24,103 --> 00:13:26,039
- You have to explain everything to them.
- Tell me about it.

373
00:13:26,105 --> 00:13:27,674
- Come on, Jung-woo.
- Yi-rang and I--

374
00:13:27,874 --> 00:13:29,142
I keep getting confused.

375
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,576
She looks like Yi-rang.

376
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:32,578
We need to act like a married couple.

377
00:13:33,112 --> 00:13:38,117
<i>Jung-woo is still traumatized</i>
<i>by what happened on that horrible day.</i>

378
00:13:38,951 --> 00:13:40,687
Our club doesn't do this,

379
00:13:40,753 --> 00:13:43,356
but some people take pictures
while doing fieldwork, right?

380
00:13:43,423 --> 00:13:46,659
- That could raise some privacy issues,
- Right.

381
00:13:46,726 --> 00:13:47,994
- That's true.
- and besides...

382
00:13:48,161 --> 00:13:48,995
It's for you.

383
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:51,798
To wipe off the oil.

384
00:13:52,532 --> 00:13:53,566
Oh my.

385
00:13:55,368 --> 00:13:56,636
Did she have dirt under her nails?

386
00:13:57,203 --> 00:13:58,271
You look good together.

387
00:13:59,138 --> 00:14:00,106
Are you...

388
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:02,642
How about here?

389
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:05,044
It looks fine.

390
00:14:05,311 --> 00:14:06,212
- Can you wipe it for me?
- Okay.

391
00:14:08,748 --> 00:14:09,716
- Here?
- Yes.

392
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:11,718
It seems fine now.

393
00:14:12,318 --> 00:14:14,687
I wish you'd be
more casual toward me, honey.

394
00:14:14,754 --> 00:14:16,255
You're always so proper and formal.

395
00:14:17,023 --> 00:14:19,225
I can't believe I have to see this.

396
00:14:19,292 --> 00:14:20,493
- Me first.
- Wait.

397
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:21,761
- Let me go first.
- Excuse me.

398
00:14:21,828 --> 00:14:23,062
- No, me first.
- No, me.

399
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:25,264
What are they doing there?

400
00:14:25,331 --> 00:14:26,966
That's for venting and complaining.

401
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:29,168
- Is that a thing here?
- Yes, it is.

402
00:14:29,268 --> 00:14:31,904
They're being
so embarrassing and pathetic.

403
00:14:32,405 --> 00:14:33,840
I can't do this anymore.

404
00:14:36,008 --> 00:14:37,744
Acting like a couple
isn't a big deal, though.

405
00:14:37,810 --> 00:14:40,046
It's not a serious issue.

406
00:14:40,113 --> 00:14:41,247
Not at all.

407
00:14:41,314 --> 00:14:43,049
As long as Jun-han
does his part, we're good.

408
00:14:43,116 --> 00:14:45,118
If you don't want to do it with Sun-i,

409
00:14:45,184 --> 00:14:46,586
Jun-han and I can do it instead.

410
00:14:47,086 --> 00:14:48,287
- I'm good with that.
- Good.

411
00:14:48,354 --> 00:14:50,690
- Let's keep this up, then.
- Come on.

412
00:14:50,757 --> 00:14:52,492
You should be looking for good properties,

413
00:14:52,558 --> 00:14:54,260
not a new husband!

414
00:14:54,327 --> 00:14:56,496
The point of this whole
real estate business

415
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:58,231
is to buy a new house for us as newlyweds.

416
00:14:58,297 --> 00:14:59,832
That's the problem with you.

417
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,135
You're driving away all our male members.

418
00:15:02,835 --> 00:15:04,504
I don't mind, as long as Jun-han stays.

419
00:15:05,171 --> 00:15:07,807
You're driving me insane.

420
00:15:08,541 --> 00:15:10,510
- Can I change seats?
- Yes, you can.

421
00:15:11,043 --> 00:15:11,978
I can't take this anymore.

422
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,914
- Eun-kyung must be having a hard time.
- That's true.

423
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:16,149
Why are you having a hard time?

424
00:15:16,215 --> 00:15:17,817
You should find yourself
a good husband too.

425
00:15:17,884 --> 00:15:20,586
No, I... Well...

426
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:24,290
What's the most important factor for you
when you're doing fieldwork

427
00:15:24,357 --> 00:15:26,025
to invest in properties?

428
00:15:26,292 --> 00:15:28,828
I usually look for parks or walking trails

429
00:15:28,895 --> 00:15:29,996
- near the area.
- Oh, parks?

430
00:15:30,062 --> 00:15:31,264
That's important.

431
00:15:31,330 --> 00:15:32,999
- Do you like to go on walks?
- Yes.

432
00:15:33,065 --> 00:15:35,334
Don't people recognize you, though?

433
00:15:36,002 --> 00:15:37,036
Not really.

434
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:38,204
- Seriously?
- Yes.

435
00:15:38,271 --> 00:15:41,207
Maybe it's hard to tell if you're
wearing a hat and a pair of headphones.

436
00:15:41,674 --> 00:15:43,176
- I don't wear hats.
- Then...

437
00:15:43,509 --> 00:15:45,411
do you just walk around like that?

438
00:15:46,012 --> 00:15:48,014
- Yes.
- What about in Japan?

439
00:15:49,849 --> 00:15:50,917
Ms. Eun-kyung?

440
00:15:55,421 --> 00:15:56,556
They don't do it like that.

441
00:16:01,494 --> 00:16:03,463
No one recognizes me.

442
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:05,465
- Not even in Japan?
- No.

443
00:16:05,531 --> 00:16:07,567
Really? I'd recognize you in a second.

444
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:10,636
You're still quite young, Soo-jung.

445
00:16:10,703 --> 00:16:14,140
Have you had any experience
in real estate investment?

446
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:16,709
I have.

447
00:16:17,076 --> 00:16:19,212
- Is this...
- Don't lie to us.

448
00:16:20,179 --> 00:16:21,781
- Is this a real estate club?
- Don't lie to us.

449
00:16:21,848 --> 00:16:23,483
Yes, specifically real estate fieldwork.

450
00:16:23,549 --> 00:16:25,885
Oh, so that's why
we're talking about real estate.

451
00:16:28,187 --> 00:16:31,190
You found out just now.

452
00:16:32,692 --> 00:16:34,360
Our TV show is about real estate.

453
00:16:34,794 --> 00:16:36,762
- Oh, is that why that's the theme?
- And you play a building owner.

454
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,131
- Oh, is that why that's the theme?
- And you play a building owner.

455
00:16:39,198 --> 00:16:42,869
Were you asleep or something?
Get a hold of yourself, man.

456
00:16:42,935 --> 00:16:43,870
Sorry.

457
00:16:45,972 --> 00:16:47,206
Is that so?

458
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:51,511
For me, feng shui is
the most important factor.

459
00:16:51,577 --> 00:16:53,145
- Feng shui?
- It's really important.

460
00:16:53,212 --> 00:16:55,014
What do you look for, specifically?

461
00:16:55,081 --> 00:16:56,182
In terms of feng shui?

462
00:16:57,316 --> 00:16:58,885
Well, first...

463
00:16:59,318 --> 00:17:00,686
In my opinion...

464
00:17:05,558 --> 00:17:07,226
It needs to have good feng shui.

465
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:08,961
You don't know anything, do you?

466
00:17:10,563 --> 00:17:11,497
He's clueless.

467
00:17:11,564 --> 00:17:13,432
- Do you actually know feng shui?
- I have my instincts.

468
00:17:13,499 --> 00:17:14,500
- Your instincts?
- Your instincts?

469
00:17:14,567 --> 00:17:16,536
- Yes, I get certain feelings.
- I see.

470
00:17:16,936 --> 00:17:18,337
There are a lot of mountains

471
00:17:18,404 --> 00:17:19,772
- in Korea, right?
- Right.

472
00:17:19,939 --> 00:17:22,742
So when people are choosing places
to settle down

473
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:24,210
near those mountains,

474
00:17:24,277 --> 00:17:26,679
they have to have strategies for survival.

475
00:17:26,746 --> 00:17:29,949
So feng shui is not about
an abstract belief in the supernatural.

476
00:17:30,016 --> 00:17:33,219
If you look at the history of feng shui
in South Korea or China,

477
00:17:33,286 --> 00:17:34,453
- Yes?
- there are a lot of mountains...

478
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,822
<i>Sun-ja seeks special measures</i>

479
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:40,159
<i>when Jung-woo's lecture</i>
<i>goes on for too long.</i>

480
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:42,662
...they have to have
strategies for survival.

481
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:44,263
That's what feng shui is.

482
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:45,965
So you're thinking of feng shui

483
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:48,668
as statistics and practices
based on people's experiences?

484
00:17:49,969 --> 00:17:51,671
What is this, a documentary?

485
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:53,372
What is this, a documentary?

486
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:55,041
- No, I--
- This isn't a documentary.

487
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:56,375
- I was having fun.
- I thought he'd teach me feng shui.

488
00:17:56,442 --> 00:17:58,411
Oh, do you like discussions like that?

489
00:17:58,477 --> 00:18:01,547
I mean, they're teaching me something new.

490
00:18:01,614 --> 00:18:03,082
Exactly. We're here to share information,

491
00:18:03,149 --> 00:18:05,084
not to stuff our faces
with fried chicken, you dumbass.

492
00:18:05,151 --> 00:18:07,386
I'm not good
with these kinds of discussions.

493
00:18:08,354 --> 00:18:09,589
Why did you bring those dowsing rods?

494
00:18:09,655 --> 00:18:11,123
They're about feng shui too.

495
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:13,125
- They seek out underground water.
- Exactly.

496
00:18:13,192 --> 00:18:14,560
Why do they keep pointing at me?

497
00:18:14,627 --> 00:18:16,462
I don't know. It's weird.

498
00:18:16,529 --> 00:18:17,964
Does that mean something bad?

499
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:20,199
Yes. They do keep pointing at you.

500
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:22,034
You must have a lot of heavy metal.

501
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:24,470
- Isn't that bad?
- Do you drink tap water?

502
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:26,472
- No, I don't.
- You don't?

503
00:18:26,539 --> 00:18:28,207
Are you moving them yourself?

504
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:29,308
No, I'm not.

505
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:30,409
- They're doing that on their own.
- Really?

506
00:18:30,476 --> 00:18:31,777
- I'm serious.
- Can I try?

507
00:18:31,877 --> 00:18:33,546
Sure. Go ahead, Soo-jung.

508
00:18:33,613 --> 00:18:35,615
- Are you Christian, Sun-ja?
- Yes.

509
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:48,027
I can't believe you accused me
of having a lot of heavy metal in my body.

510
00:18:48,394 --> 00:18:49,862
Why did they stop?

511
00:18:50,029 --> 00:18:52,131
- It's pointing this way.
- Why did they stop?

512
00:18:52,431 --> 00:18:54,066
- It's stuck in this direction.
- See? I told you.

513
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,534
- What's wrong with them?
- What does it mean?

514
00:18:55,601 --> 00:18:56,936
What's going on?

515
00:18:57,003 --> 00:18:58,170
They're dowsing rods.

516
00:18:58,237 --> 00:19:01,974
Even if you hold them still,
they just move on their own.

517
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:02,975
They're just...

518
00:19:04,610 --> 00:19:06,579
- No thanks.
- It's you this time.

519
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:09,015
- No thanks.
- It's you this time.

520
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:10,650
Don't do this to me, Jung-woo.

521
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:13,686
Make up your mind, Jung-woo.

522
00:19:13,753 --> 00:19:15,554
- I think...
- This is hard.

523
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:19,091
I think they just point
at someone you want to beat up.

524
00:19:20,693 --> 00:19:22,995
Someone you hate the most.

525
00:19:23,062 --> 00:19:28,968
What do you look for when you're
looking at properties, Soo-jung?

526
00:19:30,202 --> 00:19:31,604
I go with my feelings, too.

527
00:19:31,671 --> 00:19:33,239
- Really?
- A feeling of warmth?

528
00:19:33,305 --> 00:19:34,507
Do you get bad feelings too?

529
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:36,075
- Yes, absolutely.
- Seriously?

530
00:19:36,142 --> 00:19:37,877
And if you go to sleep
in one of those places,

531
00:19:37,943 --> 00:19:39,779
- you get sleep paralysis.
- Right.

532
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:40,913
- Right?
- Totally.

533
00:19:40,980 --> 00:19:42,081
- I've had that a lot.
- Really?

534
00:19:42,148 --> 00:19:43,849
- Really?
- Yes, so I--

535
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,452
Have you ever lived
in a place with a bad vibe?

536
00:19:47,219 --> 00:19:48,187
This was...

537
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:55,227
when I moved into an apartment unit that
was over 30 <i>pyeong</i> for the first time.

538
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:57,063
For some strange reason,

539
00:19:57,129 --> 00:19:58,597
I couldn't sleep in my bedroom.

540
00:19:58,664 --> 00:19:59,899
- Because of the bad vibes?
- Yes.

541
00:20:00,132 --> 00:20:01,133
One day,

542
00:20:01,734 --> 00:20:04,737
I found myself
in front of the master bathroom.

543
00:20:04,804 --> 00:20:06,439
Like a sleepwalker,

544
00:20:06,505 --> 00:20:09,141
I was just staring blankly
at the bathroom.

545
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,443
- Oh no!
- Gosh.

546
00:20:15,281 --> 00:20:17,917
After that, I couldn't
sleep in that room anymore,

547
00:20:17,983 --> 00:20:20,519
so I moved my bed to a smaller room

548
00:20:20,586 --> 00:20:22,888
- across from my old bedroom.
- Right.

549
00:20:22,955 --> 00:20:25,024
Only then could I fall asleep.

550
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:27,226
That was scary.

551
00:20:27,293 --> 00:20:29,128
Have you experienced
something like that too?

552
00:20:29,195 --> 00:20:31,063
- Not at my own place.
- Really?

553
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:33,766
I was attending some overseas event once,

554
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:39,105
and there were a lot of fans
who were calling my name.

555
00:20:39,371 --> 00:20:42,641
After the event,
I went back to my hotel room to sleep,

556
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:44,677
but I fell into a sleep paralysis

557
00:20:44,744 --> 00:20:46,946
and I felt someone choking me

558
00:20:47,012 --> 00:20:49,615
- and calling my name like my fans did.
- Oh gosh.

559
00:20:49,782 --> 00:20:52,752
That's a scary one.

560
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:54,386
Later, I found out

561
00:20:54,453 --> 00:20:58,124
that the hotel we stayed in
was famous for being haunted.

562
00:20:58,691 --> 00:21:00,993
So now I always check in advance

563
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,829
- whether the hotel is haunted.
- Just in case?

564
00:21:03,896 --> 00:21:05,798
- You do some research beforehand?
- Yes.

565
00:21:06,165 --> 00:21:07,666
- You can look it up online.
- Really?

566
00:21:07,733 --> 00:21:10,503
- So I avoid those kinds of hotels now.
- Really?

567
00:21:11,303 --> 00:21:13,005
- It happens sometimes.
- That's scary.

568
00:21:13,072 --> 00:21:15,374
I used to be in a band, and...

569
00:21:15,441 --> 00:21:17,076
Oh, that's right!

570
00:21:17,143 --> 00:21:20,746
But our band's practice room

571
00:21:20,813 --> 00:21:23,516
was in some deep, dark corner.

572
00:21:23,582 --> 00:21:25,518
- We used to practice there.
- Right.

573
00:21:25,584 --> 00:21:28,521
- And one day, I fell asleep there,
- Yes?

574
00:21:28,921 --> 00:21:30,623
and had an out-of-body experience.

575
00:21:31,257 --> 00:21:32,958
- An out-of-body experience?
- Yes.

576
00:21:34,326 --> 00:21:35,861
- An out-of-body experience?
- You could see yourself?

577
00:21:35,928 --> 00:21:37,396
- Yes.
- Did you look down on yourself?

578
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:38,497
I'd never experienced it before,

579
00:21:38,564 --> 00:21:39,899
but I felt myself rise

580
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,101
- Oh my.
- and go out into the lounge area.

581
00:21:42,168 --> 00:21:44,303
- Really?
- Yes, really.

582
00:21:44,770 --> 00:21:47,439
Can you float to the kitchen now
and bring us two colas?

583
00:21:48,007 --> 00:21:50,209
- Go on, float out of your body.
- Like this?

584
00:21:50,276 --> 00:21:52,077
- I'm floating.
- He's floating!

585
00:21:52,511 --> 00:21:53,612
Just like this.

586
00:21:54,246 --> 00:21:55,247
- Just like this.
- There he goes.

587
00:21:55,848 --> 00:21:57,283
Oh my goodness.

588
00:21:57,349 --> 00:21:59,285
- Just like this.
- That's so funny.

589
00:21:59,351 --> 00:22:01,020
You go along with everything, Jun-han.

590
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:03,622
My husband does
everything I ask him to do.

591
00:22:03,689 --> 00:22:05,858
He's such a sweet guy.

592
00:22:08,294 --> 00:22:10,930
- We've all come a long way
- Right.

593
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:13,799
since we first started the Legwork Club.

594
00:22:13,866 --> 00:22:15,901
- We've all made it in real estate.
- Exactly.

595
00:22:15,968 --> 00:22:18,470
So maybe we could do some legwork
for other things too.

596
00:22:18,537 --> 00:22:20,372
There are so many options.

597
00:22:20,439 --> 00:22:22,141
I had to do some legwork to buy

598
00:22:22,208 --> 00:22:23,943
- those Dubai chewy cookies.
- Yes, you did.

599
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:26,078
How about doing legwork
for things we like?

600
00:22:26,745 --> 00:22:27,880
What do you like?

601
00:22:28,047 --> 00:22:29,114
Me?

602
00:22:29,181 --> 00:22:30,549
- I like...
- We could do legwork...

603
00:22:30,616 --> 00:22:31,750
I like plush toys.

604
00:22:31,817 --> 00:22:33,586
- Plush toys?
- Plush toys?

605
00:22:33,986 --> 00:22:35,020
What kind of plush toys?

606
00:22:35,387 --> 00:22:37,189
- Oh my goodness!
- What's that?

607
00:22:37,256 --> 00:22:38,891
- Oh my goodness!
- What's that?

608
00:22:38,958 --> 00:22:41,260
Isn't that you, Jung-woo?

609
00:22:41,327 --> 00:22:42,928
- Do you always carry it around?
- Yes.

610
00:22:42,995 --> 00:22:45,297
- Why does it look like a potato?
- It's my guardian angel.

611
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:47,199
- That potato toy is your guardian angel?
- Yes.

612
00:22:47,266 --> 00:22:48,934
Do you like claw machine games, too?

613
00:22:49,168 --> 00:22:50,069
I did at one point.

614
00:22:50,135 --> 00:22:51,170
- Did you do it often?
- I spent a lot of money on them.

615
00:22:51,237 --> 00:22:52,071
Really?

616
00:22:52,137 --> 00:22:54,773
Whenever I play
a claw machine game, I'd think,

617
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:57,409
"There has to be some <i>yaro</i>,
or a shady secret behind it."

618
00:22:57,843 --> 00:22:59,545
- You get what I mean?
- A nostalgic word choice.

619
00:22:59,612 --> 00:23:02,281
- What on earth is <i>yaro?</i>
- Is that word not fine to use?

620
00:23:02,348 --> 00:23:03,949
- I really don't know what it is.
<i>- Yaro?</i>

621
00:23:06,785 --> 00:23:07,920
- Yes, <i>yaro.</i>
<i>- Yaro?</i>

622
00:23:09,355 --> 00:23:10,189
Yes.

623
00:23:10,556 --> 00:23:13,158
In other words, some shady secret

624
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:15,227
- behind the mechanics of the machine.
- I see.

625
00:23:15,294 --> 00:23:17,329
I wanted to figure that out.

626
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:20,332
So I spent ages figuring out
how to increase my chances.

627
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:22,201
You have to look at the claw

628
00:23:22,268 --> 00:23:23,535
and the springs above it.

629
00:23:23,602 --> 00:23:26,672
- The springs?
- Yes, in the joint area, so to speak.

630
00:23:26,839 --> 00:23:28,707
That's where you have to look first.

631
00:23:28,941 --> 00:23:30,976
The older it is, the easier it is to win.

632
00:23:31,043 --> 00:23:33,879
- I see.
- So you look for machines that are older?

633
00:23:33,946 --> 00:23:35,915
If it's a new kind of claw machine,

634
00:23:35,981 --> 00:23:38,550
it has already been set
not to let you win.

635
00:23:38,617 --> 00:23:40,853
- Really?
- Yes, so it slips easily.

636
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,888
But the oil has dried up
in the older ones,

637
00:23:42,955 --> 00:23:45,357
- so they're easier to grab.
- That's a great tip.

638
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:47,326
- It really is a great tip.
- Really?

639
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:49,495
He looks like he's too cool
for stuff like this,

640
00:23:49,561 --> 00:23:52,131
so it's kind of sad to imagine him
studying claw machines.

641
00:23:53,032 --> 00:23:54,767
- So disappointing.
- Sorry.

642
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,303
Eun-kyung looks like
she likes claw machines.

643
00:23:57,369 --> 00:23:58,671
I like plush toys.

644
00:23:58,737 --> 00:24:00,172
- Which one?
- There's this character I like.

645
00:24:00,572 --> 00:24:01,840
I'll give this to you.

646
00:24:01,907 --> 00:24:03,575
- Oh, really? Thank you.
- Yes.

647
00:24:03,642 --> 00:24:04,944
She doesn't look too thrilled.

648
00:24:05,010 --> 00:24:06,078
Put it on a necklace.

649
00:24:06,545 --> 00:24:09,281
- Who puts a potato on their necklace?
- It'll be nice.

650
00:24:09,348 --> 00:24:10,849
I'll use it as a bag charm.

651
00:24:10,916 --> 00:24:12,284
- It's cute, though.
- For whenever you go out.

652
00:24:12,351 --> 00:24:13,852
Yes, it's kind of cute.

653
00:24:13,919 --> 00:24:15,254
So Jung-woo likes toys,

654
00:24:15,321 --> 00:24:16,689
- but what about the rest of you?
- I'm curious.

655
00:24:17,523 --> 00:24:18,857
I like K-pop idols.

656
00:24:18,924 --> 00:24:20,159
- Seriously?
- I do.

657
00:24:20,225 --> 00:24:21,894
- Who?
- You don't look like the type.

658
00:24:21,961 --> 00:24:22,995
Who do you like?

659
00:24:23,062 --> 00:24:24,063
Among the idols?

660
00:24:25,531 --> 00:24:26,465
Do I have to tell you?

661
00:24:26,532 --> 00:24:28,500
- I want to know!
- I'm curious!

662
00:24:29,034 --> 00:24:31,070
- She's so embarrassed.
- Tell us!

663
00:24:31,937 --> 00:24:33,405
NCT WISH.

664
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:36,108
- You like NCT WISH?
- NCT?

665
00:24:36,175 --> 00:24:39,211
So there's this NCT WISH merchandise...

666
00:24:39,278 --> 00:24:40,479
- Merchandise?
- And...

667
00:24:40,546 --> 00:24:43,983
I really wanted to buy it for myself
on my last birthday,

668
00:24:44,049 --> 00:24:47,586
so I went to a merchandise shop
in Seongsu-dong.

669
00:24:47,653 --> 00:24:49,855
- Really?
- My friends and I went there

670
00:24:49,922 --> 00:24:52,658
- to look around the shop, and...
- Right.

671
00:24:52,725 --> 00:24:55,694
- There's this star-shaped plush toy
- Right.

672
00:24:56,028 --> 00:24:59,898
that was part of the album merchandise,

673
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:02,668
and every fan wants to get one
however they can

674
00:25:03,035 --> 00:25:04,336
for the artist they like.

675
00:25:04,403 --> 00:25:06,171
- Official merchandise.
- That's so sweet.

676
00:25:06,238 --> 00:25:09,475
But I'd rather go alone.

677
00:25:09,541 --> 00:25:10,376
Hey.

678
00:25:10,442 --> 00:25:12,678
- Why? Are you embarrassed by us?
- She means it.

679
00:25:12,745 --> 00:25:14,046
- No, it's not that.
- What is it?

680
00:25:14,813 --> 00:25:17,783
I'm the one who's embarrassed.

681
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:20,586
- You want to focus on that person.
- I want to get passionate about it alone.

682
00:25:20,652 --> 00:25:23,489
It'd be too embarrassing to do it
in front of others.

683
00:25:23,555 --> 00:25:24,690
That's so cute.

684
00:25:24,757 --> 00:25:26,725
I'm sure the NCT WISH members
would love it too.

685
00:25:26,792 --> 00:25:28,093
- I'm sure.
- Would they watch this?

686
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,829
- Of course they would!
- Of course!

687
00:25:30,896 --> 00:25:32,564
- She's blushing!
- That was so cute.

688
00:25:32,631 --> 00:25:34,366
- Send them a video message.
- She's blushing!

689
00:25:34,433 --> 00:25:36,268
- They're going to see this!
- Really?

690
00:25:36,335 --> 00:25:37,336
After this,

691
00:25:37,403 --> 00:25:38,871
they'll send you
their merchandise themselves.

692
00:25:38,937 --> 00:25:39,772
Really?

693
00:25:40,439 --> 00:25:43,442
- She's still holding your potato.
- NCT WISH...

694
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:46,311
I like you a lot.

695
00:25:47,179 --> 00:25:48,347
What's with the potato?

696
00:25:48,414 --> 00:25:51,750
I especially love your song, "Steady."

697
00:25:53,052 --> 00:25:55,320
- This is so cute.
- She's adorable.

698
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:58,323
NCT WISH members,
please love Eun-kyung back!

699
00:25:58,390 --> 00:26:01,293
- Man, that was so lovely.
- She's so shy about it.

700
00:26:01,460 --> 00:26:02,928
Do you also agonize over which to buy?

701
00:26:02,995 --> 00:26:04,897
- She's so adorable.
- It can be agonizing.

702
00:26:04,963 --> 00:26:06,598
When I look at Soo-jung,

703
00:26:06,665 --> 00:26:10,202
I get the feeling that she hasn't had
much hardship in her life. Right?

704
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:11,737
How could you possibly know that?

705
00:26:11,804 --> 00:26:13,839
- She just looks so classy and serene.
- Come on, now.

706
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:16,075
Didn't you work really hard
when you were an idol?

707
00:26:16,141 --> 00:26:17,409
Oh, back then?

708
00:26:17,576 --> 00:26:18,677
- You must have.
- I think so.

709
00:26:18,744 --> 00:26:21,647
Maybe that's true, because I honestly
can't remember much

710
00:26:21,713 --> 00:26:23,348
- from that time,
- Really?

711
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:25,184
- when I was in my teens.
- Because you worked too hard.

712
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:27,252
You were in your teens back then?

713
00:26:27,319 --> 00:26:30,489
Isn't being an actress
a completely different experience

714
00:26:30,556 --> 00:26:31,757
from being a singer?

715
00:26:31,824 --> 00:26:33,158
Yes, it's very different.

716
00:26:33,225 --> 00:26:35,961
Which one demanded more of you?

717
00:26:36,829 --> 00:26:39,998
For me, I find acting a bit harder

718
00:26:40,065 --> 00:26:43,168
- because I started it later.
- I see.

719
00:26:43,235 --> 00:26:45,904
- I see.
- I need to draw out a lot of emotions.

720
00:26:46,772 --> 00:26:48,273
When the camera is on me,

721
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:50,209
I need to use everything I have

722
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:52,044
- to go all in.
- Right. You need to focus.

723
00:26:52,111 --> 00:26:53,779
- You really need to go all in.
- Yes.

724
00:26:53,879 --> 00:26:56,014
- You know, one time,
- The schedules can be different.

725
00:26:56,081 --> 00:26:58,617
- I did a TV show with Soo-jung.
- What?

726
00:26:58,984 --> 00:26:59,985
- Really?
- You don't remember?

727
00:27:00,052 --> 00:27:01,854
It's like Sun-ja has lived two lifetimes.

728
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,722
She's done everything and met everyone.

729
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:04,890
- What was the show?
- You won't believe it.

730
00:27:06,125 --> 00:27:07,659
<i>My Lovely Girl.</i>

731
00:27:08,594 --> 00:27:10,562
- Was Sun-ja lovely in that show?
- Do you remember?

732
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:12,097
- Yes, I remember that show.
- We did it together.

733
00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:15,567
<i>Sun-ja's character</i>
<i>looked down on Soo-jung's character.</i>

734
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:17,136
Thank you for remembering.

735
00:27:17,202 --> 00:27:18,737
- Did you not like me back then?
- No, things were fine between us.

736
00:27:18,804 --> 00:27:19,771
Do you mean it?

737
00:27:19,838 --> 00:27:21,907
We also did a film together, didn't we?

738
00:27:22,107 --> 00:27:24,076
- Really? You were in so many things.
- Of course.

739
00:27:24,143 --> 00:27:26,311
I'm going to be upset
if you say you don't remember.

740
00:27:27,346 --> 00:27:28,413
Was it <i>Miss Mommy?</i>

741
00:27:29,248 --> 00:27:30,582
- Sorry?
<i>- Miss Mommy?</i>

742
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:32,885
- It's actually called <i>Miss Granny.</i>
<i>- Miss Granny.</i>

743
00:27:34,453 --> 00:27:36,188
What's "Miss Mommy"?

744
00:27:36,255 --> 00:27:38,624
I'm an idiot.
My brain feels frozen right now

745
00:27:38,824 --> 00:27:40,125
- after an all-nighter.
- Oh no.

746
00:27:41,093 --> 00:27:42,961
Which film was it?

747
00:27:43,028 --> 00:27:43,996
<i>The Princess and the Matchmaker.</i>

748
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:47,099
- Oh, that's right!
- Who did you play in that film?

749
00:27:47,166 --> 00:27:49,601
<i>Sun-ja played Mal-nyeon,</i>
<i>a woman looking for love.</i>

750
00:27:49,768 --> 00:27:51,570
<i>She still hasn't found it.</i>

751
00:27:51,637 --> 00:27:53,405
- Do you remember?
- Yes, I do.

752
00:27:53,472 --> 00:27:54,973
- You remember, right?
- Oh no.

753
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:57,042
- What's with the "oh no"?
- I'm so sorry.

754
00:27:57,109 --> 00:27:59,044
- I'm sorry.
- You don't have to apologize.

755
00:27:59,178 --> 00:28:01,313
What's the hardest thing
you've done, Jun-han?

756
00:28:01,413 --> 00:28:02,781
- The hardest thing?
- Yes.

757
00:28:02,848 --> 00:28:04,116
It's acting for me too.

758
00:28:04,216 --> 00:28:06,185
- Really?
- All actors seem to feel the same.

759
00:28:06,251 --> 00:28:07,319
I want to be better at it.

760
00:28:07,386 --> 00:28:08,820
I used to study acting

761
00:28:08,887 --> 00:28:10,756
by watching Jung-woo's works too.

762
00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:12,191
What did you watch?

763
00:28:12,257 --> 00:28:14,026
A film called <i>Beastie Boys.</i>

764
00:28:16,195 --> 00:28:18,063
That was an amazing film.

765
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:20,632
The one where he goes,
"I love you, you fucking bitch!"

766
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:23,368
The one where he goes,
"I love you, you fucking bitch!"

767
00:28:24,570 --> 00:28:27,072
Was that the one?

768
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:28,774
That's the one.

769
00:28:28,974 --> 00:28:30,375
It sounds so crass, but--

770
00:28:30,442 --> 00:28:31,577
She's going there again!

771
00:28:31,643 --> 00:28:34,346
She's leaving us again!

772
00:28:34,413 --> 00:28:36,381
It feels like Eun-kyung has spent

773
00:28:36,448 --> 00:28:38,217
