774
00:28:38,283 --> 00:28:40,485
- I guess she enjoys her alone time.
- Yes.

775
00:28:40,552 --> 00:28:43,522
That scene is seared into my memory.

776
00:28:43,589 --> 00:28:46,858
His acting was so real in that film

777
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:48,660
- that it felt like a documentary.
- It was.

778
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:51,129
Then you must've been so thrilled

779
00:28:51,196 --> 00:28:52,598
when you met him in person.

780
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:54,399
- I couldn't believe it.
- I see.

781
00:28:54,466 --> 00:28:55,400
Weren't you nervous?

782
00:28:55,467 --> 00:28:56,668
I'm still nervous, actually.

783
00:28:56,735 --> 00:28:57,736
- Really?
- Yes.

784
00:29:00,172 --> 00:29:02,407
He's lying. Why would he be nervous?

785
00:29:02,608 --> 00:29:04,042
What's there to be nervous about?

786
00:29:04,610 --> 00:29:05,611
Then answer me this.

787
00:29:05,677 --> 00:29:07,813
Are you more nervous being near Jung-woo

788
00:29:07,879 --> 00:29:10,249
or being near me? Tell me.

789
00:29:12,551 --> 00:29:15,020
It's obviously Sun-ja.

790
00:29:15,254 --> 00:29:17,589
Honestly, I think I was
a bit more nervous...

791
00:29:17,656 --> 00:29:18,624
- Being near me?
- Yes.

792
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:24,029
You're below me, Ha Jung-woo.

793
00:29:24,096 --> 00:29:25,831
- I'm right here,
- Is it...

794
00:29:25,897 --> 00:29:28,433
- Is it an impression of Kim Sang-joong?
- and you're here.

795
00:29:32,471 --> 00:29:34,873
How was it for you
when you were young, Jung-woo?

796
00:29:34,940 --> 00:29:36,375
- It was tough.
- What did you do?

797
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:37,409
I taught people how to act.

798
00:29:37,476 --> 00:29:39,344
- You really did that as a job?
- Really?

799
00:29:39,411 --> 00:29:41,046
- You taught others how to act?
- Yes, I was an acting tutor.

800
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:42,347
How old were your students?

801
00:29:43,048 --> 00:29:44,116
High school seniors.

802
00:29:44,283 --> 00:29:45,550
- Those prepping for acting school?
- That's cool.

803
00:29:45,617 --> 00:29:47,419
What kind of stuff did you teach them?

804
00:29:48,053 --> 00:29:50,455
I'd advise them on
which schools they can apply to,

805
00:29:50,522 --> 00:29:51,723
depending on their grades.

806
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:54,293
Can you pretend I'm one of your students?

807
00:29:54,559 --> 00:29:56,094
- It depends...
- Hello, sir.

808
00:29:56,161 --> 00:29:57,429
Hello, sir.

809
00:29:57,663 --> 00:29:59,264
I was told that

810
00:29:59,331 --> 00:30:01,366
you could help me
get into a good acting school.

811
00:30:01,433 --> 00:30:02,501
- That's right.
- Right.

812
00:30:02,567 --> 00:30:04,303
- Yes.
- So what do I have to do?

813
00:30:04,903 --> 00:30:07,372
Where on earth is she going with this?

814
00:30:09,107 --> 00:30:10,409
- First, take a seat.
- Okay.

815
00:30:12,878 --> 00:30:15,013
Let's see your free acting first.

816
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:16,581
Free acting? What should I do?

817
00:30:16,715 --> 00:30:17,816
How about Lady Macbeth?

818
00:30:17,883 --> 00:30:19,117
Lady Macbeth?

819
00:30:19,885 --> 00:30:21,853
It suits you,
since you have a Western vibe.

820
00:30:22,754 --> 00:30:24,456
I do?

821
00:30:27,025 --> 00:30:29,194
How much do your lessons cost, sir?

822
00:30:29,261 --> 00:30:30,662
- My lessons?
- Yes.

823
00:30:30,996 --> 00:30:34,232
It depends
on your parents' financial status.

824
00:30:34,299 --> 00:30:36,001
I'll charge you accordingly.

825
00:30:36,134 --> 00:30:37,069
It's different for everyone?

826
00:30:37,202 --> 00:30:38,537
It's flexible pricing.

827
00:30:39,471 --> 00:30:42,674
If your family's not well off,
I can give you a discount.

828
00:30:42,741 --> 00:30:44,509
We're not well off.

829
00:30:45,577 --> 00:30:47,312
Then just pay me what you can.

830
00:30:47,379 --> 00:30:48,380
Did you really do that?

831
00:30:48,447 --> 00:30:49,815
- I actually did that.
- Really?

832
00:30:49,881 --> 00:30:51,416
- That's impressive.
- So cool.

833
00:30:51,683 --> 00:30:53,719
- Tell me about it.
- So cool!

834
00:30:53,785 --> 00:30:56,021
Jung-woo recently directed
and starred in a film

835
00:30:56,088 --> 00:30:57,989
- called <i>The People Upstairs</i>, right?
- Yes.

836
00:30:58,123 --> 00:31:00,392
I really enjoyed that film.

837
00:31:00,459 --> 00:31:01,727
DIRECTOR HA'S EXPERIMENTAL, UNIQUE PIECE
I watched it so many times.

838
00:31:01,793 --> 00:31:03,228
- Me too.
- Probably more than five times.

839
00:31:03,295 --> 00:31:04,496
I first watched it in the theater,

840
00:31:04,563 --> 00:31:05,731
then I bought it myself--

841
00:31:05,797 --> 00:31:07,599
- I'll give you an autograph.
- I watched it a lot.

842
00:31:09,801 --> 00:31:11,103
- So my question is...
- Thank you.

843
00:31:11,169 --> 00:31:12,003
What is it?

844
00:31:12,971 --> 00:31:15,040
Why was it a flop at the box office?

845
00:31:15,173 --> 00:31:17,109
Why was it a flop at the box office?

846
00:31:17,175 --> 00:31:19,077
- Well...
- It wasn't a "flop," but...

847
00:31:23,849 --> 00:31:26,151
- Let's just say it didn't do very well.
- It wasn't successful either.

848
00:31:26,218 --> 00:31:27,652
How exactly did it do in the box office?

849
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:28,787
It brought in 530,000 viewers.

850
00:31:28,854 --> 00:31:30,655
- That's pretty good, isn't it?
- No.

851
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:31,757
It could've been better.

852
00:31:32,057 --> 00:31:35,293
Like a fool, we chose to release it
at the same time as <i>Zootopia 2</i>.

853
00:31:36,361 --> 00:31:37,629
That was a bad move.

854
00:31:37,696 --> 00:31:39,664
- You were up against <i>Zootopia?</i>
<i>- Zootopia...</i>

855
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:42,334
We had no chance against <i>Zootopia 2.</i>

856
00:31:42,401 --> 00:31:44,936
- But I think...
- We were completely filled

857
00:31:45,003 --> 00:31:46,438
with conceit and arrogance at the time.

858
00:31:46,505 --> 00:31:48,540
It was followed by <i>Avatar: Fire and Ash</i>.

859
00:31:48,607 --> 00:31:50,275
- That was bad luck.
- Good grief.

860
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:56,481
You go all in on love, don't you?

861
00:31:57,315 --> 00:32:00,619
Love is the only thing I go all out on.

862
00:32:00,852 --> 00:32:02,387
She's such a romantic.

863
00:32:02,587 --> 00:32:03,922
I'm like that.

864
00:32:04,122 --> 00:32:05,991
Don't you think you should feel

865
00:32:06,057 --> 00:32:09,161
completely crazy over someone
at least once in your life?

866
00:32:09,227 --> 00:32:11,430
- You should.
- Have you all experienced that?

867
00:32:11,496 --> 00:32:14,433
...completely crazy over someone
at least once in your life?

868
00:32:14,766 --> 00:32:16,601
Have you all experienced that?

869
00:32:16,802 --> 00:32:18,870
- I have.
- You really have?

870
00:32:19,171 --> 00:32:20,539
Jun-han is a romantic too.

871
00:32:20,605 --> 00:32:22,808
- You're making me jealous again.
- I...

872
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:24,576
- When was this?
- Sorry. It was a long time ago.

873
00:32:24,643 --> 00:32:25,544
- Fine, then.
- Okay.

874
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:28,280
From what I've seen,
Jun-han is such a sweet guy.

875
00:32:28,413 --> 00:32:30,415
He seems like he'd do anything you want

876
00:32:30,482 --> 00:32:32,250
- and support you no matter what.
- Exactly.

877
00:32:32,317 --> 00:32:33,318
He's a romantic guy.

878
00:32:33,385 --> 00:32:36,421
I think I used to be like that before,

879
00:32:36,721 --> 00:32:38,490
but I've used up all my energy.

880
00:32:38,857 --> 00:32:40,325
Now I can't do that anymore.

881
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:41,827
- It's different now.
- I can relate.

882
00:32:41,893 --> 00:32:44,796
There are people
who like to play a bit hard to get

883
00:32:44,863 --> 00:32:47,132
in a calculating sort of way,

884
00:32:47,199 --> 00:32:50,001
and there are people
who are just straightforward and honest,

885
00:32:50,068 --> 00:32:52,637
telling you everything they feel
deep down, you know?

886
00:32:52,704 --> 00:32:54,639
- Like in your navel?
- What?

887
00:32:54,806 --> 00:32:56,708
- Like in your navel?
- What?

888
00:32:56,775 --> 00:32:57,976
No, never mind.

889
00:32:58,043 --> 00:33:00,445
