1048
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:50,295
Please?

1049
00:38:50,829 --> 00:38:53,031
- You can take a shower, and...
- And then?

1050
00:38:53,531 --> 00:38:54,833
Can't you go to a sauna?

1051
00:38:56,134 --> 00:38:57,669
But today,

1052
00:38:57,735 --> 00:38:59,370
my mom is coming over.

1053
00:38:59,437 --> 00:39:01,206
- Your mother is coming over?
- Yes.

1054
00:39:01,272 --> 00:39:03,641
Then can you give me money
so I can go to a bathhouse?

1055
00:39:04,542 --> 00:39:05,543
What?

1056
00:39:06,244 --> 00:39:07,946
Don't you earn 70 million won a year?

1057
00:39:08,012 --> 00:39:11,015
I do, but I'm saving up
to buy a second car.

1058
00:39:11,683 --> 00:39:12,817
That sounds awful.

1059
00:39:12,884 --> 00:39:15,019
- This won't work.
- It won't?

1060
00:39:15,086 --> 00:39:16,654
She's already had enough.

1061
00:39:16,721 --> 00:39:18,089
It won't? Then the next scenario.

1062
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:19,390
This guy owns a house.

1063
00:39:20,825 --> 00:39:21,826
We're by the Han River.

1064
00:39:21,893 --> 00:39:23,094
A BOYFRIEND WHO ONLY OWNS A HOUSE

1065
00:39:23,661 --> 00:39:25,330
- Isn't the sunset beautiful?
- It is.

1066
00:39:25,396 --> 00:39:27,098
We should be drinking wine.

1067
00:39:27,565 --> 00:39:28,800
Can you buy me some?

1068
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:31,236
Get Makiki Sauvignon Blanc.

1069
00:39:32,637 --> 00:39:33,638
Get Makiki Sauvignon Blanc.

1070
00:39:35,240 --> 00:39:36,941
- Sure, I can do that.
- Thank you.

1071
00:39:37,008 --> 00:39:38,910
- Let's get it delivered, then.
- Okay.

1072
00:39:39,677 --> 00:39:41,613
- I want this too.
- This is a little...

1073
00:39:41,679 --> 00:39:43,681
We don't have a sofa, right?
Can you buy me one?

1074
00:39:43,748 --> 00:39:45,316
We don't have a sofa, right?
Can you buy me one?

1075
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:46,317
- A sofa?
- Yes.

1076
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:47,418
I own this house,

1077
00:39:47,485 --> 00:39:49,087
but I couldn't furnish it.

1078
00:39:51,356 --> 00:39:52,323
But...

1079
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:54,626
That's my house, but it's empty.

1080
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:56,160
- You don't have any furniture?
- No.

1081
00:39:56,227 --> 00:39:57,695
I think it'll be fine without furniture.

1082
00:39:57,762 --> 00:39:59,631
I'm worried you'll be uncomfortable there.

1083
00:39:59,931 --> 00:40:01,833
- I'm not coming over.
- That's not it either.

1084
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:04,068
- You're not coming over?
- No, I'm not.

1085
00:40:04,135 --> 00:40:06,170
Which one would you pick, though?

1086
00:40:08,139 --> 00:40:10,842
- I don't know. Help me out here.
- You have to choose.

1087
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:12,443
- You have to pick one to date.
- Going all out.

1088
00:40:13,111 --> 00:40:15,280
Come on. Make your choice.

1089
00:40:15,546 --> 00:40:17,048
Their looks would matter here.

1090
00:40:17,515 --> 00:40:18,483
They're both her ideal type.

1091
00:40:18,783 --> 00:40:20,018
- Both of them?
- Yes.

1092
00:40:22,186 --> 00:40:23,855
Why am I thinking about this so seriously?

1093
00:40:23,922 --> 00:40:25,423
Because it's a serious question.

1094
00:40:25,490 --> 00:40:27,558
- We're all serious about this too.
- I'm serious about this.

1095
00:40:27,625 --> 00:40:30,428
- This feels like an important question.
- It really is.

1096
00:40:30,495 --> 00:40:32,263
We're all serious about this too.

1097
00:40:32,330 --> 00:40:33,998
- It became serious.
- We're thinking about it too.

1098
00:40:34,065 --> 00:40:35,633
- I'm almost in tears now.
- We're all serious about this.

1099
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:38,069
Yes, we're all serious about this.

1100
00:40:38,136 --> 00:40:39,203
What are your main concerns?

1101
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:41,205
Tell me what you're worried about, honey.

1102
00:40:41,706 --> 00:40:44,676
Well, you seem to have
no financial responsibility at all.

1103
00:40:44,742 --> 00:40:45,944
Teach it to me, then.

1104
00:40:46,311 --> 00:40:47,645
- What?
- Teach it to me.

1105
00:40:47,712 --> 00:40:49,213
- Teach what?
- Financial responsibility.

1106
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,381
For crying out loud.

1107
00:40:52,817 --> 00:40:54,686
Look at me, honey.

1108
00:40:56,854 --> 00:40:58,556
Let's stop seeing each other.

1109
00:40:58,623 --> 00:41:00,191
Let's have someone else have a turn.

1110
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:02,694
Of the two-- Hey, wait!

1111
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,629
- Hey, wait!
- What?

1112
00:41:05,029 --> 00:41:06,230
- What's wrong?
- She looked so fresh...

1113
00:41:06,364 --> 00:41:08,766
She looked so fresh
and vivacious at first,

1114
00:41:08,967 --> 00:41:11,569
- so where's all that energy now?
- No, I...

1115
00:41:11,636 --> 00:41:14,038
When I looked over at her,
her face just filled with dread.

1116
00:41:14,105 --> 00:41:16,507
Doesn't she look like this right now?

1117
00:41:21,379 --> 00:41:24,716
Then how about this?
You said you liked NCT WISH, right?

1118
00:41:24,782 --> 00:41:26,484
- One of its members--
- Exactly.

1119
00:41:26,551 --> 00:41:28,453
Let's say you get to live

1120
00:41:28,886 --> 00:41:30,054
with one of them.

1121
00:41:30,121 --> 00:41:31,723
- Say that--
- No, I can't do that.

1122
00:41:31,789 --> 00:41:32,790
- Why not?
- No.

1123
00:41:32,857 --> 00:41:34,459
- You can't do it?
- I can't do it.

1124
00:41:34,525 --> 00:41:36,260
Why can't you live with him?

1125
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:38,062
- I can't.
- Why not?

1126
00:41:38,129 --> 00:41:40,365
- If you have to live with...
- I just want to watch from afar.

1127
00:41:40,698 --> 00:41:41,599
That's fine with me.

1128
00:41:41,666 --> 00:41:44,402
- Fine, then don't think it's about him.
- Okay.

1129
00:41:44,469 --> 00:41:47,939
Let's say you're so in love with a man

1130
00:41:48,006 --> 00:41:50,675
